segment.source: You can change, repair, or remove the Microsoft Diagnostics and Recovery Toolset (DaRT) 10 installation by double-clicking the DaRT 10 installation file and then clicking the button that corresponds to the action that you want to perform.
segment.target: You can change, repair, or remove the Microsoft Diagnostics and Recovery Toolset (DaRT) 10 installation by double-clicking the DaRT 10 installation file and then clicking the button that corresponds to the action that you want to perform.

segment.source: You can also change, repair, or remove the DaRT installation using the Windows Control Panel by completing the following steps.
segment.target: You can also change, repair, or remove the DaRT installation using the Windows Control Panel by completing the following steps.

segment.source: To change, repair, or remove DaRT
segment.target: To change, repair, or remove DaRT

segment.source: Click Start, and then click Control Panel.
segment.target: Click Start, and then click Control Panel.

segment.source: On Control Panel, navigate to the feature that lets you uninstall programs.
segment.target: On Control Panel, navigate to the feature that lets you uninstall programs.

segment.source: Click Microsoft Diagnostics and Recovery Toolset 10, and then click the button that corresponds to the action that you want to perform.
segment.target: Click Microsoft Diagnostics and Recovery Toolset 10, and then click the button that corresponds to the action that you want to perform.
